  "texts": [
    "The absence of metacognitive capabilities in LLMs raises questions about whether such capabilities should be expected.",
    "Comprehensive models of cognition, such as the transtheoretical model 31 incorporate external factors, including interactions with team members or databases, which could be implemented for LLMs with Retrieval Augmented Generation 31.",
    "While external factors might partially compensate for the lack of internal metacognition, this approach presents limitations.",
    "Although it aligns with human oversight requirements in healthcare, it may not fully address the complexity required in LLM-based systems for critical decision-making.",
    "For instance, a summarization agent retrieving patient record information might fail to recognize incomplete contextual data, potentially generating inaccurate summaries."
  ],
